Doc Spatz, I commend you.  Now you know a little bit of what we experienced.  Tearing the scabs away instead of picking at them started my healing.  The infection is cleaned and the healing starts. I told you that when in Vietnam I did the best job that I could do for an eighteen year old boy with little or no wordly experiences. This sounds to me that you were doing the best job that you knew how to do. I didn't have the education qualifications to enter college.  If I had perhaps, like you, the influences around me would have given me some distance from reality of the war. Also a different view of the war.  Thanks for sharing.  Doc Del wants Part II.  I, too, would like to hear more.  I don't have any questions but I do listen good. <br><br>

<p><code>-- cbotkins@visuallink.com  (Chet Botkins) </code><p>


